../lnet/lnet/lnet options: &apos;lnet_peer_discovery_disabled=0 ip2nets=&quot;tcp(eth0) 192.168.2.[30-44/2]; tcp(eth1) 192.168.2.[31-45/2]&quot; accept=all&apos;
In file included from &amp;lt;command-line&amp;gt;:32:0:
/home/hornc/fs2/lustre/../lnet/include/uapi/linux/lnet/lnetctl.h:26:10: fatal error: linux/lnet/lnet-types.h: No such file or directory
 #include &amp;lt;linux/lnet/lnet-types.h&amp;gt;
          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
compilation terminated.
 sanity-lnet test_300: @@@@@@ FAIL: cannot compile &apos;/home/hornc/fs2/lustre/../lnet/include/uapi/linux/lnet/lnetctl.h&apos;
&lt;/pre&gt;
